    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've prepared:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Stepper Compound Component\n\n### What will be created\n\n**4 files touched (2 new, 2 edited):**\n\n| File | Action |\n|------|--------|\n| `ui/stepper.tsx` | **CREATE** |\n| `examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | **CREATE** |\n| `ui/_registry.ts` | **EDIT** (add 1 entry) |\n| `examples/_registry.ts` | **EDIT** (add 1 entry) |\n\n---\n\n### Architecture of `stepper.tsx`\n\nThe component uses **two React contexts** — the same pattern as `carousel.tsx`:\n- **`StepperContext`** (root → all) — broadcasts `activeStep` + `orientation`\n- **`StepperItemContext`** (item → children) — broadcasts `step` number\n\n**CVA** (`stepperTriggerVariants`) styles the trigger circle's 3 states: `completed`, `active`, `pending`.\n\n**Key state logic:**\n- `StepperItem` computes `data-state` = `\"completed\"` if `step < activeStep`, `\"active\"` if equal, `\"pending\"` if greater\n- `StepperSeparator` is `\"completed\"` when `activeStep > step` (i.e., the next step has been reached)\n- `StepperContent` returns `null` when `step !== activeStep`\n\n### Placement in registries\n- UI registry: inserted alphabetically between `\"spinner\"` and `\"switch\"`, dependency: `[\"class-variance-authority\"]`\n- Example registry: inserted after the last `spinner-*` entry, `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"]`\n\n### Demo\nA 3-step horizontal wizard (Account → Profile → Complete) with clickable triggers, Next/Previous buttons, and per-step content panels — all inside a single `<Stepper>` root so context flows to `StepperContent`.",
